Any data subject can contact our data protection officer directly, at any time, with any questions, suggestions, or requests regarding data protection and your data. You can request that we delete your data by contacting Kanopy’s data protection officer, or you can learn how utilize Kanopy’s self-service options for data deletion at
Kanopy’s Help Center
.
2. What do we do with your personal data?
a. When you use our websites, our services (including our apps), or contact us
The provision of our websites and our services may require the processing of personal data, such as your IP address. This processing is necessary for retrieving the content displayed on our websites (including various functions), our services and due to IT security measures.
You also have the option of contacting us (e.g. via our Data Request Center, etc.).
(1) Legal basis
The processing of your personal data for the provision of our websites, for the use of our services (including our apps) and for communication with us is based on our overriding legitimate interest (Art. 6 1.(f) GDPR).
In order to provide this website and our services, it is technically necessary for us to process certain personal data (e.g. the IP address).
For your communication with us, it is necessary that we handle your respective personal data.
(2) Balancing of interests
As part of the necessary balancing of interests, we have weighed up your interest in confidentiality and our interests in providing our websites and our services and in making contact with you. Otherwise, we would not be able to provide you with this website or our services or respond to your contact request.
(3) Categories of recipients
We use service providers such as AWS and Azure cloud providers to provide our services. We transmit personal data to these service providers. We contractually oblige these service providers to exercise the same level of care in handling personal data as we do. Our cloud providers are based in the USA. We do not offer the option of hosting data elsewhere.
b. Use of our services
You can usually use our services without having to provide us with much personal information.
To use most Services, all you need to provide is your name, a valid library card or school ID, and an e-mail address. However, we may collect and store personal information related to your interactions and use of our Services that is necessary to provide our Services (such as your IP address, device type, library card number, and viewing history).
We also design our service in a way that makes it easy and user-friendly to use. For example, we personalize our services to better reflect certain interests and preferences of the user.
We sync last viewed/played point across devices to enable a viewing journey that spans multiple devices. Email addresses submitted to Kanopy to create an End User Account are stored by Kanopy, and are used as login credentials so that you can enjoy a personalized Kanopy experience. If, upon account registration, you have affirmatively indicated that you would like to receive messages from Kanopy, we utilize your email address in order to contact you about new content being added to our platform, changes being implemented to the platform, and to respond to your requests for help.
If you have location permission enabled when using Kanopy, we may determine your general geographic location using GPS coordinates so we can provide localized content. Kanopy determines your geographic location using your IP address so we can help you find nearby schools and/or libraries, as well as provide you with access to the appropriate content for the country or territory in which you are located.
We also process personal data to ensure stable, high-quality operation and improvement of our services. For this purpose, we analyze error messages, check network communication, take IT security measures, check user authentication, personalize content and generally in the context of providing library and school or educational services at your institution.
(1) Legal basis
We may process your personal data to perform a relevant contract (Art. 6 1(b) GDPR). In this case, the processing of your personal data is necessary to provide you with our services under the relevant contract.
The processing of your personal data for the user-friendly design and use of our services is also based on our overriding legitimate interest (Art. 6 1(b) GDPR).
We process your location data based on your consent (Art. 6 1.(a) GDPR).
Depending on local law, we process personal data of students using Kanopy based on the consent of their parent or guardian as determined by their educational institution.
(2) Balancing of interests
As part of the necessary balancing of interests, we have weighed up your interest in confidentiality and our interests in providing and optimizing user-friendly and application-friendly services. Otherwise, we would not be able to offer you a user-friendly design and application of our services or optimize them accordingly and ensure the corresponding functionality.
(3) Categories of recipients
We use service providers such as AWS and Azure cloud providers to provide our services. We transmit personal data to these service providers. We contractually oblige these service providers to exercise the same level of care in handling personal data as we do. Our cloud providers are based in the USA. We do not offer the option of hosting data elsewhere.
c. Marketing and advertising communication
Kanopy only sends marketing and advertising communications to those End Users who have opted-in to receive such messages. If you provide consent to receive marketing and advertising communications from Kanopy, we may use your contact information for marketing purposes, promotional communications and product and customer surveys.
Your consent is the legal basis for the processing of your corresponding personal data (Art. 6 1.(a) GDPR).
You may change your preferences for receiving newsletters, promotional offers, product updates, product and customer surveys, and other communications initiated by Kanopy by following an unsubscribe link in a marketing email.
d. When you apply to us
You can apply to us. For this purpose, we process the personal data that you provide to us as part of your application.
We process your personal data for the initiation, execution and processing of the corresponding contract (Art. 6 1(b) GDPR).
e. If we sell or restructure our business and/or a service
We reserve the right to sell or restructure our company and/or a service in whole or in part. We may transfer your personal data to a third party in the future, in compliance with the respective data protection requirements. We will inform you of this with a notice period of at least 30 days, with reference to the consequences for continued use of our services.
(1) Legal basis
The processing of your personal data in the context of such a sale or restructuring is based on our overriding legitimate interest (Art. 6 1.(f) GDPR). In order to process a corporate transaction or corporate restructuring, it may be necessary for us to transfer your respective personal data to a third party.
(2) Balancing of interests
As part of the necessary balancing of interests, we have weighed up your interest in confidentiality and our interests in a corresponding sale or restructuring. We would otherwise not be able to complete such a sale or restructuring.
(3) Categories of recipients
We may also transfer your personal information to a new legal owner of our business and its assets as part of a sale agreement for our business.
f. If we anonymize your personal data
We anonymize your personal data in order to evaluate it for statistical purposes.
(1) Legal basis
The processing of your personal data within the scope of such anonymization is based on our overriding legitimate interest (Art. 6 1.(f) GDPR).
(2) Balancing of interests
As part of the necessary balancing of interests, we have weighed up your interest in confidentiality and our interest in appropriate anonymization. We would not be able to achieve such anonymization otherwise. The GDPR does not apply to anonymous data.
(3) Categories of recipients
We may use service providers for the anonymization process. For this purpose, we transmit personal data to these service providers. These service providers are contractually obliged by us to exercise the same level of care in handling personal data as we do.
g. If you allow the use of cookies/identifiers and analysis tools in your browser
We use cookies/identifiers and analysis tools to provide our website and our services.
So-called “cookies”
are used on our services and in our services. Cookies are data records that are stored by a web server on the user’s end device (e.g. computer, smartphone, tablet). When our website is accessed again using the same end device, these are sent back either to our website (
“first party cookie”
) or to another website to which the cookie belongs (
“third party cookie”
).
Various information can be used as identifiers (e.g. your browser version).
Legal basis
The legal basis for the use of
technically necessary cookies/identifiers
is our legitimate interest in connection with a statutory provision (Section 25 Para. 2 No. 2 TTDSG, Art. 6 Para. 1 lit. f) GDPR).
The storage of information in your terminal equipment or the access to information already stored in your terminal equipment is absolutely necessary in order for us to be able to provide the telemedia service expressly requested by you as a user.
Otherwise, the legal basis is generally your consent if no specific legal basis is mentioned below (Section 25 Para. 1 TTDSG, Art. 6 Para. 1 lit. a) GDPR). You can revoke your consent at any time, e.g. by deleting cookies set via the browser settings of your device. Please note that for technical reasons, this procedure only applies to the specific device used and you can update your consent at a later date.
Settings for cookies / identifiers:
You can revoke your consent at any time with effect for the future as follows:
You can update/change your cookie settings, via your web browser, at any time on any Kanopy website by clicking on your username in the upper right hand corner of the website, and then navigating down in the menu to the link labeled "Cookies".
You can also prevent the collection and processing of your personal data by preventing the storage of third-party cookies on your device and by deactivating the execution of script code in your browser.
(1) Use of Google Analytics
We use Google Analytics, a web analysis service provided by Google LLC, 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA (
“Google ”
) on our websites.
Google Analytics uses so-called “cookies”, text files that are stored on your device and that enable an analysis of your use of our respective website.
The information generated by the cookie about your use of our websites is usually transferred to a Google server in the USA and stored there. However, by activating IP anonymization, your IP address will be shortened beforehand by Google within member states of the European Union or in other contracting states to the Agreement on the European Economic Area.
Only in exceptional cases will the full IP address be transmitted to a Google server in the USA and shortened there. Google will use this information on our behalf to evaluate your use of our services, to compile reports on website activity and to provide us with other services relating to website activity and internet usage. The IP address transmitted by your browser as part of Google Analytics will not be merged with other Google data.
You can prevent the storage of cookies by setting your browser software accordingly; however, we would like to point out that in this case you may not be able to use all functions on our website to their full extent.
In addition, you can prevent Google from collecting the data generated by the cookie and relating to your use of the website (including your IP address) and from processing this data by downloading and installing the browser plug-in available under the following link:
http://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout
We continue to use Google Analytics to evaluate data from the respective Double-Click cookies and also from Google Ads for statistical purposes. If you do not want this, you can deactivate it using the following manager:
https://myadcenter.google.com/home
You can find an overview of the data Google collects here:
https://privacy.google.com/businesses/adsservices/
Google is certified under the EU-US Data Privacy Framework:
https://dataprivacyframework.gov/list
(2) Use of Google Tag Manager
We use the Google Tag Manager of Google LLC, 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA (“
Google
”). You can find information about this tool here:
https://marketingplatform.google.com/intl/en/about/tag-manager/
With Google Tag Manager, tags from Google and third-party services can be managed and bundled and embedded on an online presence. Tags are small code elements on an online presence that are used, among other things, to measure visitor numbers and behavior, and to test and optimize online presences. When a user visits the online presence, the current tag configuration is sent to the user's browser. This contains instructions on which tags should be triggered. Google Tag Manager triggers other tags, which in turn may collect data. Information about this can be found in the sections on the use of the corresponding services in this privacy policy. Google Tag Manager does not access this data.
You can find more information about Google Tag Manager here:
https://support.google.com/tagmanager/?hl=en#topic=15191151
You can find Google’s privacy policy here:
https://policies.google.com/privacy.
You can prevent Google from collecting the data generated by the cookie and relating to your use of the website (including your IP address) and from processing this data by downloading and installing the browser plug-in available under the following link:
https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout
You can deactivate the use of your personal data by Google using the following link:
https://adssettings.google.de?hl=en
For more information on objection and removal options against Google, please visit:
https://policies.google.com/privacy?gl=DE&hl=en
