(3) Google Firebase
We use Google Firebase to analyze our services and to check them for malfunctions in order to operate our websites and services in the most user-friendly way possible. Google Firebase is an analysis tool that provides insights into the respective usage and functionality. You can find further details here:
https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy
Google is certified under the EU-US Data Privacy Framework:
https://dataprivacyframework.gov/list
(4) Use of YouTube
We use the provider YouTube to embed videos. YouTube is operated by YouTube LLC, with headquarters at 901 Cherry Avenue, San Bruno, CA 94066, USA (“
YouTube
”). YouTube is represented by Google.
We use YouTube plug-ins on some of our websites. When you visit websites that contain such a plug-in, a connection is established to the YouTube servers and the plug-in is displayed. This transmits to the YouTube server which of our websites you have visited. If you are logged in as a YouTube member, YouTube assigns this information to your personal user account. When you use the plug-in, for example by clicking the start button of a video, this information is also assigned to your user account. You can prevent this assignment by logging out of your YouTube user account and other user accounts of YouTube, LLC and Google before using our websites and deleting the corresponding cookies from the companies.
Further information on data processing and data protection information by YouTube (Google) can be found at:
https://policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en
Google (including YouTube) is certified under the EU-US Data Privacy Framework:
https://dataprivacyframework.gov/list
3. Content Delivery Networks
We use providers of content delivery networks to display relevant content on our websites. For this purpose, we may transmit personal data (e.g. IP address) to these providers.
The providers are:
- CacheFly
- CloudFlare
Some of these providers also process your personal data outside the EU/EEA (see the section “
Data transfer to third countries
” below).
(1) Legal basis
The processing of your personal data for the non-personalized presentation of the content is based on our overriding legitimate interest (Art. 6 1.(f) GDPR). In order to provide our websites and our services, it is necessary for us to process certain personal data (e.g. the IP address).
We process your personal data to provide personalized content based on your consent (Art. 6 1.(a) GDPR). You can revoke your consent at any time with effect for the future.
(2) Balancing of interests
As part of the necessary balancing of interests, we have weighed up your interest in confidentiality and our interest in providing the relevant content. In each case involving the processing of your personal data to provide you with personalized content, your interest in confidentiality takes precedence. In each case involving the processing of your personal data to provide you with non-personalized content, Kanopy’s legitimate interest takes precedence. Otherwise we would not be able to make our websites (including the content) available to you.
4. How long do we store your personal data?
We delete your personal data if the respective purpose of storage no longer applies and no legal provision requires retention (e.g. a retention obligation under a tax code and/or a commercial code).
If deletion is not possible in individual cases, processing will be restricted. Personal data of users of our services for schools and educational institutions will be retained by Kanopy only for the period necessary to support the authorized school or educational institution.
Finally, the storage period also depends on the statutory limitation periods.
5. What rights do you have as a data subject?
To exercise your rights and to withdraw your consent, please use the contact details provided above.
a) You have the right to request information about all personal data that we process about you at any time.
b) If your personal data is incorrect or incomplete, you have the right to have it corrected and supplemented.
c) You can request the deletion of your personal data at any time, unless we are legally obliged or authorized to further process your data.
d) If the legal requirements are met, you can request that the processing of your personal data be restricted.
e) You have the right to object to the processing if the data processing is carried out for the purposes of direct advertising or profiling. If the processing is based on a balance of interests, you can object to the processing by stating reasons arising from your particular situation.
f) If the data processing is carried out on the basis of your consent or within the framework of a contract, you have the right to transfer the data you have provided, provided that this does not affect the rights and freedoms of other persons.
g) If we process your data on the basis of a declaration of consent, you have the right to revoke this consent at any time with effect for the future. The processing carried out before the revocation remains unaffected by the revocation.
h) You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority at any time if you believe that data processing has been carried out in violation of applicable law (Art. 77 GDPR). The contact information for the data protection supervisory authority in your member state can be found here:
https://www.edpb.europa.eu/about-edpb/about-edpb/members_en#member-ie
We will inform all recipients to whom we have disclosed personal data of any rectification or erasure of your personal data or restriction of corresponding processing, unless doing so should prove impossible or involve disproportionate expenditure. We will inform you of the recipients applicable to you if you request this.
6. In what context do we create automatic profiles?
We do not create automatic profiles. However, we do create user profiles in accordance with the services you use.
7. Data transfer to the United States
(1) Recipients in The United States
We use service providers such as AWS and Azure cloud providers to provide our services. We transfer personal data to these service providers. These service providers are contractually obliged to exercise the same level of care in handling personal data as we do. Our cloud providers are based in the USA. We do not offer the option of hosting data elsewhere.
The legal basis for such data transfer is generally your consent or the respective performance of a contract or the use of EU standard data protection clauses or the EU-US data protection framework, extension of the UK to the EU-US DPF and Swiss-US data protection directive in accordance with Article 44 GDPR.
You can download the template for EU standard data protection clauses here:
https://ec.europa.eu/info/law/law-topic/data-protection/international-dimension-data-protection/standard-contractual-clauses-scc_de
.
(2) EU-US Data Privacy Framework, UK extension to the Data Privacy Framework and Swiss-US Data Privacy Framework
In addition to and consistent with our other privacy notices, Kanopy adheres to the required principles of the EU-US Data Privacy Framework, the UK Extension to the EU-US Data Privacy Framework, and the Swiss-US Data Privacy Framework as set forth by the US Department of Commerce.
You can find more information about the principles we follow here:
Data Privacy Framework (DPF) Principles
This privacy notice complies with the EU-US Data Privacy Framework principles with respect to personal data transferred from the European Union and the United Kingdom and Switzerland.
(3) International Data Transfer Agreement
In addition, Kanopy has adopted the International Data Transfer Agreement (“
IDTA
”) to protect international transfers of personal information from the United Kingdom to the United States. You can find more information here:
https://ico.org.uk/for-organisations/uk-gdpr-guidance-and-resources/international-transfers/international-data-transfer-agreement-and-guidance/
8. Data security
We take appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect the personal data we process against accidental or intentional manipulation, loss, destruction or against access by unauthorized persons.
We use technical and organizational measures to ensure the confidentiality of your personal data and to protect it from manipulation, loss and destruction. The storage and transfer of personal data is subject to strict security precautions. Our relevant employees are trained in data protection law. They only access personal data to the extent necessary.
9. Policies and practices in all markets
This statement is intended for user convenience in markets within the EU/EEA and in markets that wish to see our policies in light of GDPR-like regulations. Our services are subject to all of our policies, terms, contracts with individual clients and in accordance with local regulations in all jurisdictions.
